HEADWORD: Neo-Hellenism
<hw>Ne`o-Hel"len*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Hellenism as
surviving or revival in modern times; the practice or pursuit of ancient
Greek ideals in modern life, art, or literature, as in the
Renaissance.</def>⟦br⟧
